<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="494" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="8.[164,612,425,476]" box="[164,301,425,446]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">
<emphasis box="[164,301,425,446]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">
<typeStatus box="[164,216,425,446]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Type</typeStatus>
species
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[164,612,425,476]" box="[164,612,455,476]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">
<taxonomicName authority="Bitner &amp; Cohen, 2015" authorityName="Bitner &amp; Cohen" authorityYear="2015" box="[164,437,455,476]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Terebratulidae" genus="Ebiscothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="bellonensis" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[164,437,455,476]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Ebiscothyris bellonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[445,612,455,476]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[164,779,533,799]" box="[164,276,533,554]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">
<emphasis box="[164,276,533,554]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[164,779,533,799]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Medium-sized terebratulide; outline subpentagonal; surface smooth; anterior commissure strongly and broadly unisulcate; beak suberect; deltidial plates conjunct; foramen circular, of medium size; cardinal process distinct, semi-elliptical; crural processes blunt and directed ventrally; hinge plates narrow and triangular; loop short, with broad descending branches and broad, medially folded, transverse band.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[164,779,854,938]" box="[164,283,854,875]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">
<emphasis box="[164,283,854,875]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[164,779,854,938]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Referring to the cruise, EBISCO, during which the specimens were collected.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[164,780,993,1902]" box="[164,265,993,1014]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">
<emphasis box="[164,265,993,1014]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[164,780,993,1902]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">
The strongly unisulcate anterior commissure of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bitner &amp; Cohen, 2015" authorityName="Bitner &amp; Cohen" authorityYear="2015" box="[164,298,1054,1075]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Terebratulidae" genus="Ebiscothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[164,298,1054,1075]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Ebiscothyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[304,400,1055,1076]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differentiates it from other extant members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="GRAY" authorityYear="1840" box="[354,525,1085,1107]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Terebratulidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="family">Terebratulidae</taxonomicName>
, which are commonly rectimarginate to weakly uniplicate. The only terebratulid genus with a similarly unisulcate anterior commissure is 
<taxonomicName authority="Laurin, 1997" authorityName="Laurin" authorityYear="1997" box="[396,714,1177,1199]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Terebratulidae" genus="Kanakythyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[396,550,1177,1198]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Kanakythyris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Laurin B" box="[561,714,1177,1199]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" pagination="411 - 471" refId="ref11285" refString="Laurin B. 1997. Brachiopoda: brachiopodes recoltes dans les eaux de la Nouvelle-Caledonie et des iles Loyaute, Matthew et Chesterfield. In: Crosnier A, ed. Resultats des Campagnes MUSORSTOM, vol. 18. Paris: Memoires du Museum nationale d'Histoire naturelle, 176: 411 - 471." type="journal article" year="1997">Laurin, 1997</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from around 
<collectingCountry box="[258,438,1207,1229]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
and the Norfolk Ridge, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laurin" authorityYear="1997" box="[164,314,1238,1259]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Terebratulidae" genus="Kanakythyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[164,314,1238,1259]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Kanakythyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clearly differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Bitner &amp; Cohen, 2015" authorityName="Bitner &amp; Cohen" authorityYear="2015" box="[540,676,1238,1259]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Terebratulidae" genus="Ebiscothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[540,676,1238,1259]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Ebiscothyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[683,780,1239,1260]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in beak and loop characters (
<bibRefCitation author="Laurin B" box="[478,621,1269,1291]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" pagination="411 - 471" refId="ref11285" refString="Laurin B. 1997. Brachiopoda: brachiopodes recoltes dans les eaux de la Nouvelle-Caledonie et des iles Loyaute, Matthew et Chesterfield. In: Crosnier A, ed. Resultats des Campagnes MUSORSTOM, vol. 18. Paris: Memoires du Museum nationale d'Histoire naturelle, 176: 411 - 471." type="journal article" year="1997">Laurin, 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bitner MA" box="[632,769,1269,1291]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" pagination="1 - 39" refId="ref10091" refString="Bitner MA. 2009. Recent brachiopods from the Norfolk Ridge, New Caledonia, with descriptions of four new species. Zootaxa 2235: 1 - 39." type="journal article" year="2009">Bitner, 2009</bibRefCitation>
). The parallel descending branches and broad medially folded transverse bands of the 
<taxonomicName authority="Bitner &amp; Cohen, 2015" authorityName="Bitner &amp; Cohen" authorityYear="2015" box="[547,680,1330,1351]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Terebratulidae" genus="Ebiscothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[547,680,1330,1351]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Ebiscothyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[685,780,1330,1351]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
loop resembles those of the terebratulid genera 
<taxonomicName authority="Cooper, 1983" authorityName="Cooper" authorityYear="1983" box="[164,481,1391,1412]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Terebratulidae" genus="Acrobrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[164,310,1391,1412]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Acrobrochus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cooper GA" box="[322,481,1391,1412]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" pagination="1 - 413" refId="ref10962" refString="Cooper GA. 1983. The Terebratulacea (Brachiopoda), Triassic to Recent: a study of the brachidia (loops). Smithsonian Contributions to Paleobiology 50: 1 - 413." type="journal article" year="1983">Cooper, 1983</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Cooper, 1977" authorityName="Cooper" authorityYear="1977" box="[498,774,1391,1413]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Terebratulidae" genus="Erymnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[498,601,1392,1413]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Erymnia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cooper GA" box="[614,774,1391,1412]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" pagination="1 - 211" refId="ref10938" refString="Cooper GA. 1977. Brachiopods from the Caribbean Sea and adjacent waters. Studies in Tropical Oceanography 14: 1 - 211." type="journal article" year="1977">Cooper, 1977</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Cooper, 1977" authorityName="Cooper" authorityYear="1977" box="[164,420,1422,1443]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Terebratulidae" genus="Tichosina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[164,270,1422,1443]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Tichosina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cooper GA" box="[277,420,1422,1443]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" pagination="1 - 211" refId="ref10938" refString="Cooper GA. 1977. Brachiopods from the Caribbean Sea and adjacent waters. Studies in Tropical Oceanography 14: 1 - 211." type="journal article" year="1977">Cooper, 1977</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Cooper, 1983" authorityName="Cooper" authorityYear="1983" box="[432,726,1422,1443]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Terebratulidae" genus="Dolichozygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[432,575,1422,1443]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Dolichozygus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cooper GA" box="[582,726,1422,1443]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" pagination="1 - 413" refId="ref10962" refString="Cooper GA. 1983. The Terebratulacea (Brachiopoda), Triassic to Recent: a study of the brachidia (loops). Smithsonian Contributions to Paleobiology 50: 1 - 413." type="journal article" year="1983">Cooper, 1983</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cooper, 1983" authorityName="Cooper" authorityYear="1983" box="[164,466,1452,1473]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Terebratulidae" genus="Dysedrosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[164,294,1452,1473]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Dysedrosia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cooper GA" box="[306,466,1452,1473]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" pagination="1 - 413" refId="ref10962" refString="Cooper GA. 1983. The Terebratulacea (Brachiopoda), Triassic to Recent: a study of the brachidia (loops). Smithsonian Contributions to Paleobiology 50: 1 - 413." type="journal article" year="1983">Cooper, 1983</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but unlike these genera 
<taxonomicName authority="Bitner &amp; Cohen, 2015" authorityName="Bitner &amp; Cohen" authorityYear="2015" box="[164,317,1483,1504]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Terebratulidae" genus="Ebiscothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[164,317,1483,1504]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Ebiscothyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[326,435,1483,1504]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
clearly differs in external morphology and lacks well-defined and distinctive crural bases (
<bibRefCitation author="Cooper GA" box="[342,511,1544,1565]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" pagination="1 - 211" refId="ref10938" refString="Cooper GA. 1977. Brachiopods from the Caribbean Sea and adjacent waters. Studies in Tropical Oceanography 14: 1 - 211." type="journal article" year="1977">Cooper, 1977</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cooper GA" box="[529,697,1544,1566]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" pagination="1 - 413" refId="ref10962" refString="Cooper GA. 1983. The Terebratulacea (Brachiopoda), Triassic to Recent: a study of the brachidia (loops). Smithsonian Contributions to Paleobiology 50: 1 - 413." type="journal article" year="1983">Cooper, 1983</bibRefCitation>
). Like 
<taxonomicName authority="Bitner &amp; Cohen, 2015" authorityName="Bitner &amp; Cohen" authorityYear="2015" box="[164,309,1575,1596]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Terebratulidae" genus="Ebiscothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[164,309,1575,1596]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Ebiscothyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[317,423,1575,1596]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, some dyscolioids are deeply unisulcate (e.g. 
<taxonomicName authority="Thomson, 1927" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1927" box="[340,660,1605,1627]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Dyscoliidae" genus="Abyssothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[340,480,1605,1626]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Abyssothyris</emphasis>
Thomson, 1927
</taxonomicName>
), but their loop has very narrow descending branches and an anteriorly rounded transverse band (
<bibRefCitation author="Cooper GA" box="[541,685,1667,1688]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" pagination="1 - 413" refId="ref10962" refString="Cooper GA. 1983. The Terebratulacea (Brachiopoda), Triassic to Recent: a study of the brachidia (loops). Smithsonian Contributions to Paleobiology 50: 1 - 413." type="journal article" year="1983">Cooper, 1983</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Laurin B" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" pagination="411 - 471" refId="ref11285" refString="Laurin B. 1997. Brachiopoda: brachiopodes recoltes dans les eaux de la Nouvelle-Caledonie et des iles Loyaute, Matthew et Chesterfield. In: Crosnier A, ed. Resultats des Campagnes MUSORSTOM, vol. 18. Paris: Memoires du Museum nationale d'Histoire naturelle, 176: 411 - 471." type="journal article" year="1997">Laurin, 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bitner MA" box="[235,380,1697,1719]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" pagination="15 - 32" refId="ref10008" refString="Bitner MA. 2006. Recent brachiopods from the Fiji and Wallis and Futuna Islands, Southwest Pacific. In: Justine J. L. and Richer de Forges B., eds. Tropical Deep-Sea Benthos, 24. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle 193: 15 - 32." type="journal article" year="2006">Bitner, 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 2008; Lee, 2006), differing markedly from 
<taxonomicName authority="Bitner &amp; Cohen, 2015" authorityName="Bitner &amp; Cohen" authorityYear="2015" box="[280,419,1728,1749]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Terebratulidae" genus="Ebiscothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[280,419,1728,1749]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Ebiscothyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[426,527,1728,1749]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, which has the broad, medially folded transverse band characteristic of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lee &amp; Smirnova, 2006)" baseAuthorityName="Lee &amp; Smirnova" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[164,616,1789,1811]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Terebratulidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="family">Terebratulidae (Lee &amp; Smirnova, 2006)</taxonomicName>
. Overall, morphology of the shell and loop lead us to allocate 
<taxonomicName authority="Bitner &amp; Cohen, 2015" authorityName="Bitner &amp; Cohen" authorityYear="2015" box="[164,299,1850,1871]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Terebratulidae" genus="Ebiscothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[164,299,1850,1871]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="494">Ebiscothyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[305,401,1850,1871]" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lee &amp; Smirnova" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[479,641,1850,1872]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Terebratulidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="family">Terebratulidae</taxonomicName>
rather than to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fischer &amp; Oehlert" authorityYear="1891" box="[242,376,1880,1902]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Dyscoliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="8" pageNumber="494" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="family">Dyscoliidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
